  "title": "feat(autocomplete): leverage scoped results",
  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThis is a revamp of the `connectAutocomplete` connector leveraging scoped results (#3964). \r\n\r\nSince this is a complete rewrite of how the connector works, I took this opportunity to migrate it to TypeScript.\r\n\r\n### Options changes\r\n\r\nThe [`indices`](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/autocomplete/js/#connector-param-render-indices) option doesn't exist anymore and is inferred by the widgets tree. If the option is used in development mode, a warning is raised.\r\n\r\n### Structure change of an autocomplete index\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n interface AutocompleteIndex {\r\n-  label: string;\r\n   index: string;\r\n   hits: Hits;\r\n   results: SearchResults | undefined;\r\n }\r\n```\r\n\r\nOnce we introduce the concept of index IDs, we might want to add it so that users can make a difference from indexes having the same name:\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n interface AutocompleteIndex {\r\n-  label: string;\r\n+  indexId: string;\r\n-  index: string;\r\n+  indexName: string;\r\n   hits: Hits;\r\n   results: SearchResults | undefined;\r\n }\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Preview\r\n\r\n[See story →](https://deploy-preview-3975--instantsearchjs.netlify.com/stories/?path=/story/autocomplete--default)\r\n\r\n## Related\r\n\r\n- [Current `connectAutocomplete` documentation](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/autocomplete/js/)\r\n- [Scoped results feature](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/pull/3964)",
